---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Debug Mode">
  <div class="docs-container">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1 class="page-title">Debug Mode</h1>
      <p class="page-description">
        Enable debug mode to get insights into your application's reactivity during development.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="docs-content">
      <nav class="docs-nav">
        <ul>
          <li><a href="#enable-debug">Enabling Debug Mode</a></li>
          <li><a href="#signal-logging">Signal Logging</a></li>
          <li><a href="#effect-logging">Effect Logging</a></li>
          <li><a href="#performance">Performance Tracking</a></li>
          <li><a href="#warnings">Warnings</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>

      <main class="docs-main">
        <section id="enable-debug" class="doc-section">
          <h2>Enabling Debug Mode</h2>
          
          <p>Debug mode helps you understand what's happening with signals, effects, and services in your application. It's automatically disabled in production builds.</p>

          <h3>Method 1: In Code</h3>
          <pre><code>{`import { enableDebug } from '@astro-dx/core';

// Enable all debug features
enableDebug();

// Or enable specific features
enableDebug({
  logSignals: true,
  logEffects: true,
  logServices: false,
  showWarnings: true
});`}</code></pre>

          <h3>Method 2: Via localStorage (Persistent)</h3>
          <p>Open your browser's DevTools console and run:</p>
          <pre><code>localStorage.setItem('astro-dx-debug', 'true');
location.reload();</code></pre>

          <h3>Disabling Debug Mode</h3>
          <pre><code>{`import { disableDebug } from '@astro-dx/core';

disableDebug();`}</code></pre>
          <p>Or clear localStorage:</p>
          <pre><code>localStorage.removeItem('astro-dx-debug');
location.reload();`}</code></pre>
        </section>

        <section id="signal-logging" class="doc-section">
          <h2>Signal Logging</h2>
          
          <p>When signal logging is enabled, you'll see every signal update in the console:</p>

          <pre><code class="console-output">{`[astro-dx:signal] count: 0 → 1
[astro-dx:signal] count: 1 → 2
[astro-dx:signal] user: {name: "John"} → {name: "Jane"}`}</code></pre>

          <div class="tip-box">
            <strong>💡 Tip:</strong> Use this to track down unnecessary re-renders or unexpected state changes.
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="effect-logging" class="doc-section">
          <h2>Effect Logging</h2>
          
          <p>Effect logging shows when effects execute and how many dependencies they track:</p>

          <pre><code class="console-output">{`[astro-dx:effect] "counter" executed with 2 dependencies (0.12ms)
[astro-dx:effect] executed with 1 dependencies (0.05ms)`}</code></pre>

          <p>To name your effects for better debugging:</p>

          <pre><code>{`effect(() => {
  console.log('Count is:', count());
}, { name: 'counter' });`}</code></pre>
        </section>

        <section id="performance" class="doc-section">
          <h2>Performance Tracking</h2>
          
          <p>You can track the performance of specific operations:</p>

          <pre><code>{`import { startPerf, endPerf } from '@astro-dx/core';

// In your code
startPerf('heavy-computation');
// ... do some work
const duration = endPerf('heavy-computation');
console.log(\`Operation took \${duration}ms\`);`}</code></pre>

          <div class="tip-box warning">
            <strong>⚠️ Warning:</strong> Performance tracking is only available when debug mode is enabled. In production, these functions are no-ops.
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="warnings" class="doc-section">
          <h2>Warnings</h2>
          
          <p>Debug mode can warn you about common issues:</p>

          <pre><code class="console-output">{`[astro-dx:warn] Effect has no reactive dependencies
[astro-dx:warn] Signal "count" updated with the same value
[astro-dx:warn] Service "CartService" registered multiple times`}</code></pre>

          <table class="warnings-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Warning</th>
                <th>Meaning</th>
                <th>Solution</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>"Effect has no reactive dependencies"</td>
                <td>The effect will never re-run</td>
                <td>Make sure the effect reads at least one signal</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>"Signal updated with the same value"</td>
                <td>Unnecessary update that won't trigger effects</td>
                <td>Use update() only when the value actually changes</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>"Service registered multiple times"</td>
                <td>Possible memory leak or duplicate initialization</td>
                <td>Register services only once, usually in layout</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </section>

        <section class="doc-section">
          <h2>Browser DevTools Integration</h2>
          
          <p>You can also toggle debug mode directly from the browser console:</p>

          <pre><code>{`// Check current state
window.__ASTRO_DX_DEBUG__  // true or false

// Toggle debug mode
window.enableAstroDxDebug()
window.disableAstroDxDebug()`}</code></pre>

          <div class="tip-box">
            <strong>💡 Pro Tip:</strong> Create a bookmarklet to quickly toggle debug mode:
            <br />
            <code>javascript:localStorage.setItem('astro-dx-debug', localStorage.getItem('astro-dx-debug') === 'true' ? 'false' : 'true');location.reload();</code>
          </div>
        </section>
      </main>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .docs-container {
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem;
    }

    .page-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
      padding-bottom: 2rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.1);
    }

    .page-title {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #60a5fa 0%, #c084fc 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .page-description {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
      color: #94a3b8;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .docs-content {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;
      gap: 3rem;
    }

    .docs-nav {
      position: sticky;
      top: 6rem;
      height: fit-content;
    }

    .docs-nav ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .docs-nav li {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .docs-nav a {
      display: block;
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      color: #94a3b8;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      transition: all 0.2s;
    }

    .docs-nav a:hover {
      color: #e2e8f0;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    }

    .docs-main {
      min-width: 0;
    }

    .doc-section {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .doc-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.875rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: #f1f5f9;
    }

    .doc-section h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem;
      color: #e2e8f0;
    }

    .doc-section p {
      color: #cbd5e1;
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .doc-section pre {
      background: #0f172a;
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      overflow-x: auto;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }

    .doc-section code {
      font-family: 'Fira Code', 'Monaco', 'Consolas', monospace;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: #e2e8f0;
    }

    .console-output {
      color: #4ade80 !important;
      background: #022c22 !important;
    }

    .tip-box {
      background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.1);
      border-left: 4px solid #60a5fa;
      padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 0 0.5rem 0.5rem 0;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      color: #e2e8f0;
    }

    .tip-box.warning {
      background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1);
      border-left-color: #f59e0b;
    }

    .warnings-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }

    .warnings-table th,
    .warnings-table td {
      padding: 1rem;
      text-align: left;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.1);
    }

    .warnings-table th {
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.5);
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #f1f5f9;
    }

    .warnings-table td {
      color: #cbd5e1;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .docs-content {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .docs-nav {
        position: static;
        order: -1;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
